# Orders Module Rules

References:

- docs/product-requirements.md
- docs/database-design.md
- docs/enums.md
- docs/user-flows.md
- docs/api-specification.md

---

# Module Purpose

Responsibilities:

- Order Tracking
- Commission Tracking
- Cashback Calculation
- Order Status Management
- User Earnings
- Balance Updates

The Orders Module is the financial core of the platform.

---

# Source Of Data

Primary Source:

Accesstrade Postback

Secondary Source:

Accesstrade Reporting API

---

Frontend is NEVER a source of truth.

Orders must never be created manually by users.

---

# Core Flow

User

↓

Generate Affiliate Link

↓

Purchase Product

↓

Accesstrade Receives Conversion

↓

Webhook Arrives

↓

Order Created

↓

Order Pending

↓

Order Approved

↓

Cashback Calculated

↓

User Balance Updated

---

# Order Entity

Represents an affiliate conversion.

Suggested fields:

- Id
- ProviderOrderId
- UserId
- AffiliateLinkId
- Provider
- OrderValue
- CommissionAmount
- CashbackAmount
- Status
- ApprovedAt
- RejectedAt
- CreatedAt
- UpdatedAt

---

# Source Of Truth

Orders table is the source of truth.

Do not derive order history from webhook logs.

Persist all orders.

---

# Provider Order Id Rules

ProviderOrderId must be unique.

Example:

```text
AT_123456789
```

Duplicate provider orders must not create duplicate records.

---

# Order Status Rules

Use enums from:

docs/enums.md

Allowed statuses:

Pending

Approved

Rejected

Cancelled

---

Lifecycle:

Pending

↓

Approved

OR

Rejected

OR

Cancelled

---

Forbidden:

Approved

↓

Pending

---

Rejected

↓

Approved

---

Cancelled

↓

Approved

---

Order status transitions must be explicit.

---

# Commission Rules

CommissionAmount

Represents amount received from provider.

Example:

```text
Commission = 100,000 VND
```

This value comes from Accesstrade.

Never calculate provider commission internally.

---

# Cashback Rules

CashbackAmount

Represents user reward.

Formula:

```text
Cashback = Commission × CashbackPercentage
```

Example:

```text
Commission = 100,000

Cashback Rate = 80%

Cashback = 80,000
```

---

Cashback percentage must come from configuration.

Never hardcode.

---

# Cashback Timing Rules

Important:

Cashback is NOT credited immediately.

Allowed:

Pending Order

↓

No Balance Change

---

Approved Order

↓

Credit Balance

---

Rejected Order

↓

No Balance Change

---

Cancelled Order

↓

No Balance Change

---

# User Balance Rules

Balance updates only occur when:

Order Status

↓

Approved

---

Never update balance during:

Pending

Rejected

Cancelled

---

# Financial Transaction Rules

Every balance update must create a transaction record.

Suggested entity:

CommissionTransaction

Fields:

- Id
- UserId
- OrderId
- Amount
- TransactionType
- CreatedAt

---

Purpose:

Auditability

Financial history

Dispute resolution

---

# Transaction Types

Use enums.

Examples:

CashbackEarned

CashbackReversed

Withdrawal

Adjustment

---

Never hardcode strings.

---

# Idempotency Rules

Critical Requirement

Webhook processing must be idempotent.

Duplicate webhook:

✓ Allowed

Duplicate balance update:

✗ Forbidden

---

Example

Webhook arrives twice

↓

Order exists

↓

Ignore duplicate processing

---

Users must never receive duplicate cashback.

---

# Duplicate Detection Rules

Use:

ProviderOrderId

as primary uniqueness key.

---

Additionally store:

ProviderEventId

if available.

---

# Webhook Update Rules

Webhook may:

Create Order

Update Order Status

Update Commission

---

Webhook must never:

Delete Order

Delete Financial Transactions

---

# Reversal Rules

If provider reverses commission:

Approved

↓

Rejected

or

Approved

↓

Cancelled

---

Create reversal transaction.

Example:

CashbackEarned

+80,000

↓

CashbackReversed

-80,000

---

Balance must remain consistent.

---

# Order Ownership Rules

Order belongs to:

User identified by Sub1.

Example:

```text
sub1=user_123
```

↓

UserId = 123

---

Never trust user-supplied order ownership.

---

# Dashboard Contribution

Orders Module provides:

- Total Earnings
- Pending Earnings
- Approved Earnings
- Cashback History

---

Dashboard calculations should come from database.

Not frontend calculations.

---

# Query Rules

All order listings must support:

Pagination

Filtering

Sorting

---

Filters:

Status

Date Range

Provider

---

# Frontend Rules

Orders Page

Responsibilities:

- View Orders
- Filter Orders
- View Cashback

---

Frontend must not:

- Calculate earnings
- Calculate balances
- Infer order status

Backend is source of truth.

---

# Required Endpoints

GET

/api/v1/orders

Purpose:

List user orders.

---

GET

/api/v1/orders/{id}

Purpose:

Order details.

---

GET

/api/v1/orders/summary

Purpose:

Order summary.

---

# Required Queries

GetOrdersQuery

GetOrderDetailQuery

GetOrderSummaryQuery

---

# Security Rules

User can access:

Own Orders Only

---

Admin can access:

All Orders

---

Never expose:

- Other user orders
- Provider secrets
- Internal audit data

---

# Logging Rules

Log:

✓ Order Created

✓ Order Approved

✓ Order Rejected

✓ Cashback Credited

✓ Cashback Reversed

✓ Duplicate Webhook

---

Never log:

✗ Tokens

✗ Secrets

✗ Sensitive user information

---

# Performance Rules

Create indexes:

- user_id
- provider_order_id
- status
- created_at

---

Use pagination always.

Never load all orders.

---

# Testing Requirements

Must Test

Order Creation

✓ New Order

✓ Duplicate Order

---

Order Status

✓ Pending

✓ Approved

✓ Rejected

✓ Cancelled

---

Cashback

✓ Correct Calculation

✓ Configurable Percentage

---

Balance Updates

✓ Approved Order Credits Balance

✓ Pending Does Not

✓ Rejected Does Not

---

Idempotency

✓ Duplicate Webhook Ignored

✓ Duplicate Cashback Prevented

---

Reversal

✓ Cashback Reversal

✓ Balance Adjustment

---

Security

✓ User Cannot View Other User Orders

✓ Admin Can View All Orders

---

